Decide how many Principal Components (PCs) you want to keep and why (2 points) Answer: I want to keep PC1 PC2 and PC3, here is why PC1: highest standard deviation: captures the most variability in data: 29.2% of the total variance is captured PC2: highest standard deviation: captures the most variability in data: 23.06% of the total variance is captured PC3: lower amount than PC1 and PC2: captures 16.85% of the total variance: cumulative of PC1, PC2 and PC3 is 69.1%.

PC4 to PC6 captures significantly less proportions of total variance.
